,Recommended,218640,34402070,Posted: 21 August,all,Andi,"Lucius is a third person 3D puzzle game where you get to kill your victims in various ways.  Basically, this game is The Omen in game form.  Even the character you control looks like Damian.Pros:Great conceptDecent story-lineGood graphics (for the time)Stealth game (if you like that sort of game)Cons:Very linearNot well optimizedA few of the puzzles are very hard to figure it outNo free range in killing your victimsEven though there are equal amounts of pro's and con's, I really liked this game.  Each new chapter brought with it a new challenge.  Find your unfortunate target and try to figure out how to kill them without being noticed.  Each kill is unique and will bring with it a new set a obstacles to overcome.  Some of the puzzles are straight forward while others requires a bit of thought.  The story continues from chapter to chapter with you picking off the staff and family members one by one and gaining new powers as you do until there is only one left and he knows who you really are.Although the story is good and the puzzles are solid, one of the things that bothered me was the fact that this game is not well optimized.  The map is not very big and most of this game takes place inside of a mansion with a very small backyard.  I think with the small size of the map it could have been optimized better.  The biggest problem I had with this game is the fact the there is no free range in killing your victims.  Meaning that there is only one way to kill that particular person and this is not subject to negotiation.  The saving grace is that each person is killed in a different way so the game won't repeat the puzzles... unlike The Witness.One a side note... originally, I had listed sex and nudity as a pro only because it comes into play in killing two of your targets but then I took it out.  Don't get me wrong, I'm not offended by sex and nudity as long as it plays into the story.  The only reason I'm mentioning this is because in Lucius II, I have it listed as a con because there's two people having sex in a bathroom, that have nothing to do with the story, for no reason at all.At the time of this review, Lucius was selling for $9.99.  Well worth it.  It's a unique story with unique ways to kill your victims."
