76561197990399454,Recommended,218640,11984848,"Posted: 5 September, 2014",all,Rixoli,"Welcome to another edition of ""A Gamer's opinion"", Where I tackle the over 300 titles in my library and sort the♥♥♥♥♥♥from the shiny:Lucius is an interesting title, it feels like an ode to ""The Omen"" series of novels/movies. The game puts you in the shoes of a young boy named Lucius whom is the son of satan or a very powerful demon at the very least. With powers including Levitation and Pyrokinesis (controlling fire), the game revolves primarily around quietly plotting the demise of your entire family and anyone connected to them (from the handyman and gardner to your parents).Pros:Very creative, and not enough titles portray the villain winning.Puzzles require a little thinking.You are rewarded for keeping in role (masking your intentions) by getting various items that help you throughout the game.Cons:The games extremely shortThe last open opponents you have are EXTREMELY difficult to the point of near infuriating if you don't know what your doingVery little replay value (except to watch the gruesome deaths everyone suffers)Conclusion: I'd give this game a 6.5/10, I'd be certainly interested to see a sequel however of an older Lucius continuing his father's agenda."
