,Recommended,218640,29155298,Posted: 9 January,all,Greg,"I finished it, and I enjoyed it, but it has some problems.First, it's extremely difficult and gives you little in terms of guidance. Unless you are absolutely exceptional at this type of game or willing to run around the mansion for hours, you will, at some point, consult a walkthrough. I had to 3 times. Just know that sometimes the right solution is absurd.Second, there are lots of little continuity errors that drove me crazy through the whole game. For example, I turned off the TV in this room, but it's on in the cutscene that follows. I started the car in the last chapter, and it's still shaking as though it's running in this one (but no sound). There were so many of these problems, I have to say it's lazy game design.Then there is the repetitive audio. This was my biggest gripe. In each chapter, each character has a set of lines they will utter at random. Truly random. Sometimes they will say a line and then say it again 3 seconds later.  Sometimes, there is only one line, and they say it every time you're anywhere near them. This also carries over to the TVs. Turn one on, and you will learn that the temperature at Thomas Point light is 60 degrees, regardless of the time of year or time of day. It's very easy to dress for the weather if you live near Thomas Point, because it never changes. I also understand why nobody is ever watching any of the TVs. By now, they have the forecast memorized, and there's nothing else on.Finally, the drawers. For a game with a thousand openable drawers, there are shockingly few interesting things in them.That's it for the most negative thumbs-up review I've ever left."
